post_text:
The 10,000 Lakes Regional went amazing for our team. We started out the day by winning our last two qualification matches of the weekend. Before lunch we had alliance selections and our alliance captian Thor picked team 2052 and 3026. We drove through our elimination matches with no problems and earned ourselves anther victory at the 10,000 Lakes Regional. We also won the Industrial Design Award, Pit Safey, Star of the Day (Piper), and runner up for the Safety Award.

post_text: The Swamp Fest has been very busy today. CPR Training, more corn hole, welding, improv, media lessons, Rail Car Design Work, and now the MOON LANDING CHALLENGE!! All seven teams also held a robot build review session where they explained their process, what they would do differently, and then answered many questions the other teams had.
